rComments: AMAZING professor.  One of the best lecturers at utsc.  Exams are tricky, but fair.  She's hot too, in a librarian sort of way, which I'm sure will make some people happy ;).

A very friendly and helpful professor. She is willing to go extra mile to enlighten her students. Lecture style is awesome because she ties everything together. Exams are very detail oriented. Have to read text carefully. Questions could be vague
An extremely nice professor who is one of the best lecturers I've ever had.  But run, run away as fast as you can if you don't want a professor who's a GPA killer.
She's really picky with details, and her questions are pretty vague. make sure you know every single detail for both her lectures and textbook.
read the textbook and memorize every little detail that you can or else you will fail the exams horribly :)

She speaks very clearly and going to class does help..if you want to get an amazing mark in this class make sure you know every little detail because her exams are quite detailed. The great thing about the prof is that she is always willing to help.

I recommend staying FAR, FAR AWAY from her classes. She's a clear lecturer, but her exams are super unfair. They test for the sort of details that you likely won't even remember if you read the texbook and lecture notes repeatedly. I probably worked harder in this class than any other in the semester that I took it, but it was my lowest mark.
Amazing lecturer, but brutal exams.  Make sure you memorize everything.
Excellent lecturer,  but if you want to do well, memorize everything on her slides.
